{"user_message": {"title": "ADR 0003 — Ledger Money-Arithmetic Module: Shipped & Green", "content": "## ADR 0003 — Currency-aware money arithmetic (add / subtract)\n\n**Status:** Accepted · **Area:** `src/features/ledger/lib` · **Relates to:** ADR 0002 (banker's rounding), ADR 0001 (input validation)\n\nThis is a shipped deliverable, not a plan. Code + tests are in the repo and the release gate is green.\n\n### Context\nADR 0002 gave the ledger `roundMoney`, but there was **no safe way to combine two money figures** — anyone needing a sum/difference would use `a + b` and reintroduce the exact IEEE-754 drift ADR 0001/0002 exist to contain (`0.1 + 0.2 → 0.30000000000000004`). Verified by inspecting `round.ts`, `amount.ts`, the barrel, and `search_code` over the ledger feature: no module did money arithmetic.\n\n### Decision\nAdded `src/features/ledger/lib/arithmetic.ts` — `addMoney(a, b, currency)` / `subtractMoney(a, b, currency)`:\n- **Integer minor-unit arithmetic** — scale each operand to integer minor units, combine in integer space, scale back. Drift never survives the round-trip ⇒ `addMoney(0.1, 0.2, \"USD\") === 0.30` exactly. Precision follows the currency (USD cents, JPY 0dp, BHD 3dp).\n- **Composes with `roundMoney`** — the final value is passed through `roundMoney(result, currency)`, so ADR 0002 stays the single source of truth for rounding & `-0→0`. No rounding logic re-implemented.\n- **Fail-loud, typed** — `MoneyArithmeticError extends RangeError` with `.code` = `not-finite` | `mixed-currency`. Extends `RangeError` so existing catch sites keep working while gaining a discriminable cause.\n- **Mixed-currency detection** — operands accept a bare `number` or a tagged `Money {amount, currency}`; a tagged operand whose currency differs is rejected. Keeps `(number, number, currency)` ergonomic while making the cross-currency contract explicit and testable.\n\n*Rejected alternatives:* rounding floats only at the end (can't undo drift already across a representable boundary); a generic N-ary `sum()` (out of scope — deferred as Task 5).\n\n### Consequences\n- **+** Drift-free, currency-aware, canonical-by-construction add/subtract; corrupt/cross-currency inputs fail loud with a typed error; `roundMoney` stays authoritative.\n- **− / residual:** module does not itself enforce `MAX_AMOUNT` ($1M, ADR 0001) — bounding sums stays a caller concern (UNVERIFIED whether an overflow guard is needed; revisit when an aggregation consumer lands). Scaling is reliable within `Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER`, well clear of the $1M ceiling.\n\n### Task breakdown\n| # | Task | Pts | Status |\n|---|------|-----|--------|\n| 1 | `addMoney`/`subtractMoney` + integer minor-unit core | 3 | ✅ implemented |\n| 2 | `MoneyArithmeticError` typed error (`extends RangeError`, `.code`) | 1 | ✅ implemented |\n| 3 | Unit tests — 6 required cases + composition + blank currency | 2 | ✅ implemented |\n| 4 | Barrel export from `features/ledger/index.ts` | 1 | ✅ implemented |\n| 5 | N-ary `sumMoney` reducer over `addMoney` | 2 | ⏸ deferred (blocked on first aggregation consumer; pairs with ADR 0002 Task 4) |\n\n**Total: 9 pts — 7 delivered this run, 2 deferred.**\n\n### Reviewer composition check (passed)\nFeeding any arithmetic result back through `roundMoney` is a **no-op (idempotent)** — proves the module emits values already canonical to the currency's minor units and composes correctly with the ADR 0002 delivery. Covered by the `composes with roundMoney` test.\n\n### Release gate — all green\n```chart\nTests passing: 34\nNew arithmetic tests: 9\nLint errors: 0\nTypecheck errors: 0\n```\n- `npm test` → **34/34 pass** (12 amount + 13 round + 9 arithmetic)\n- `eslint` clean · `tsc --noEmit` clean · `next build` succeeds\n\n**Files:** `src/features/ledger/lib/arithmetic.ts`, `arithmetic.test.ts` (new); `src/features/ledger/index.ts`, `docs/adr/0003-money-arithmetic-module.md` (updated). Build+lint+tests are green, so it meets the merge-to-master policy — a release-merge review item has been raised (architect does not self-merge). Emitted `architecture.analysis.completed` for the delivery agent.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

